Folder contains two implementations:
###########################################
###########################################

1:  first for int64 large numbers (with one file)
	files : generic_elgamal.c

    To Compile:
		$ gcc generic_elgamal.c -o elgamal -lm
    To Run:
		$ ./elgamal

    This solution is fully functioning 

###############################################################################

2: Tried to Implement for big_int1024 (1024 bit number)
	files : 
	  Big Integer Arithmatic libraries consists of following files
		- big_int1024.c
		- big_int1024.h		// contains big Integer Arithmatic functions
	  
	  Elgamal Algorithm driver (main/test) code:
		- elgamal.c

    ## And one Makefile to compile and clean 

	To Compile:
		$ make all

	To Run:
		$ ./big_elgamal.out

	To clean:
		$ make clean


  I have tested out the big integer Arithmatic, working good with minor bugs.
  Tried to implement the elgamal DSA system for 1024 bits (Partially completed)
